               From left to right, the terms in the supplier’s profit function are revenue, capacity costs, production costs, loan initiation fees, interest paid on loans, and interest earned on financial slack. The constraints are output is equal to demand (eq. [9a]), plant capacity is greater than or equal to output (eq. [9b]), sources of funds is equal to uses of funds (eq. [9c]), and loan capacity is greater than or equal to borrowing (eq. [9d]). Note that inequation (9c), capacity costs are financed every period, while production costs are financed during the period in which production takes place.

