               . Rearranging this inequality gives the sufficient condition for using a mixture of short‐ and long‐term debt shown in partaof proposition 1.

A supplier that uses all short‐term debt (ST) completely avoids the term premium but incurs higher flotation costs. These flotation costs equal the flotation cost for the second, peak‐period loan (which is the same as the flotation cost for the single, long‐term loan) plus the flotation cost for the additional, first‐period loan that is for
