               Proposition 2 establishes that the use of some short‐term debt increases the supplier’s long‐run marginal cost of supplying the off‐peak period and reduces its long‐run marginal cost of supplying the peak period. All other changes in the supplier’s and buyer’s conditions depend on this key result.

