sec.p:
The use of short‐term debt also increases the amount and cyclicality of the supplier’s total assets, which equal its operating assets plus financial slack. The supplier has a uniform investment in total assets over the cycle when it uses a single long‐term loan for financing because the difference between operating assets in the two periods exactly equals period 1’s financial slack,
