            ) to $120.29 or $114.85, but the savings do not compensate for the increase in flotation costs from $47.57 to $60.04 or $74.18. Consequently, the use of short‐term debt increases the supplier’s total financing costs by an amount that more than offsets its increase in operating profit, causing its net profit to fall.

